Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.66,0:00:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My consciousness awakened inside\Na coin locker in complete darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.04,0:00:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.60,0:00:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.61,0:00:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.95,0:00:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the blue window frame...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.13,0:00:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Gunter Milch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.83,0:00:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrested in '88 for robbing a Bavaria\NBASF Bank cash transport vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.60,0:00:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He was placed in\NBadenburg Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.17,0:00:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In '91 he escaped\Nfrom that prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.31,0:00:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In half a year, he managed to\Ncut through the iron bars of his cell
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.27,0:01:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with a nail that he had\Nfashioned into a rasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Three days later...\NHe was caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.08,0:01:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He was imprisoned again\Nin Kreiner Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.32,0:01:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But in '93 he escaped through\Nthe sewage drain pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.49,0:01:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,His prison clothes were found next to\Na nearby river, covered in raw sewage.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.36,0:01:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He was arrested while trying to rob a\NMaximillian and Co. salary delivery truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.23,0:01:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In '97, in Ingebork\NPrison's showers...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.76,0:01:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He spent a year making a hole\Nwith a spoon and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.64,0:01:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell of the toilets\Nhere is really terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.21,0:01:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I crawled through sewage pipes,\Nso I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.68,0:01:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quiet and walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.25,0:01:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What a miserable face.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Face forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.32,0:01:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe he was called Dr. Tenma,\Nor something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.96,0:01:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Get walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.16,0:01:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would've thought he'd be\Nsuch a miserable looking guy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:01:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with a face like that,\Ndevoid of any hopes or dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.39,0:03:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask you once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.36,0:03:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you deny any involvement\Nin the poisoning of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Eisler Memorial Hospital's\NDirector Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.87,0:03:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of Surgery Oppenheim,\Nand Dr. Boyer eight years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.61,0:03:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So you plan on keeping quiet\Nthroughout the interrogation...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.41,0:03:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.82,0:03:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma.. .\Nwhat do you plan to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.15,0:04:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll still be sent to trial\Neven if you stay silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.82,0:04:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no chance in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk! Why don't you tell us\Neverything and get it off your chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.84,0:04:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\NWhat's the fuss?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.04,0:04:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Milch is suffering from\Nstomach pains!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.11,0:04:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.08,0:04:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Duller!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.21,0:04:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Dr. Duller?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.98,0:04:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor is in the examination room.\NPeter swallowed the janitors' detergent!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.09,0:04:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think he's\Nchoking on vomit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.79,0:04:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.80,0:04:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.57,0:04:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it. Let's call him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.77,0:04:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.20,0:04:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you take a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.59,0:05:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Get some hot water!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.36,0:05:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And some towels\Nand a change of clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.40,0:05:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.93,0:05:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be contagious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you\Npretending to be sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Be nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.09,0:05:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the first doctor who\Nsaw through my act this quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.56,0:05:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured that I would have more chances\Nto escape if I were sent to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how I rob\Ncash transport trucks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.17,0:05:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I act like I'm sick and\Njump in front of the truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:06:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When the guards came out panicking,\Nmy friend comes out with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.41,0:06:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I never killed anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?\NWant to escape with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You have such\Na miserable face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You start to look like that\Nwhen you're in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.63,0:06:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate cramped spaces like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My consciousness awakened inside\Na coin locker in complete darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.34,0:06:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My father and mother left me in there\Nwhile they went to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.82,0:06:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept waiting to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.39,0:06:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's go to Tunisia some day"'\Nmy father and mother always said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My father said, "If work goes\Nwell today, we're going to Tunisia!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:07:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But I waited for three days\Nand they never came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.11,0:07:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My father and mother left me\Nand probably went to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.82,0:07:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get out of\Nthis cramped place and go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.02,0:07:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What a miserable face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your face has no hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.93,0:07:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have hope like I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do\Nif you're caught again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.54,0:07:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to run away again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.11,0:07:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to\Nstay quiet today, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.62,0:07:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As we do this,\Nsomething terrible will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.36,0:07:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.03,0:08:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.46,0:08:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't believe what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.33,0:08:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But I must fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.37,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Over...and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.21,0:08:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I must tell the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.51,0:08:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I sentence the accused\Nto 20 years of imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.78,0:08:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The day my father was found guilty,\Nmy way of life was decided
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.09,0:08:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,my father moved from Sudetenland\Nin Czechoslovakia to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He started a small\Nradio station in '49.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.13,0:08:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the 60s, during the Cold War,\Nmy father was arrested for spying
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the murder of\Na federal politician's secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.61,0:08:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The news caused shockwaves\Nin West German society.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My father stood\Nby his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.35,0:08:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was sentenced to\N20 years of imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.08,0:08:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother continued to fight for my\Nfather's innocence, and, in '71 , she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In '72, my father also\Nregrettably died in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In '73, when I was in the gymnasium,\Nmy father's innocence was proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.67,0:09:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,After I graduated\Nfrom Düsseldorf University,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.34,0:09:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was I was invited to join\Nthe famous Hoffmann Law Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.97,0:09:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the first case I was assigned,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.61,0:09:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I proved the innocence of\Nthe falsely accused defendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.21,0:09:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I've continued to disprove false\Nallegations in the cases I was in charge of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.02,0:09:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Fritz Verdemann, went from being the\Nson of a spy to a hero in the legal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.57,0:09:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over the Rainbow...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The radio station\Nthat my father ran
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,would always begin and\Nend everyday with that song.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.07,0:09:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To you and my father who were in the East,\Nit probably symbolized the free world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.31,0:09:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.08,0:10:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My father died in jail fighting\Nfor his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.29,0:10:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To clear away that regret, I want to be\Ninvolved in as many cases as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where the person standing trial\Nmay be falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.56,0:10:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me more\Nabout Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ilsa, how was\Nyour prenatal check-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.11,0:10:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor said that the baby\Ncould be born any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You passed by a man in the lobby,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.59,0:10:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Is he the man who\Nyou were talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.26,0:10:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Alfred Baul...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.49,0:10:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked me if I wanted to\Nrepresent Dr. Tenma with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.33,0:10:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you turn down\NDr. Tenma's case the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.37,0:10:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But that time,\Nthe client was Hans Georg Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:11:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure why that tycoon would\Nwant me to be Dr. Tenma's lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.21,0:11:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But, this time,\Na different reason became clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.88,0:11:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The clients that Mr. Baul talked about were\Npatients whose lives Dr. Tenma had saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.16,0:11:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.13,0:11:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This Dr. Tenma was definitely\Na wonderful doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.70,0:11:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you\Ntake up the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.87,0:11:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If I win the case, I can receive\Na large reward from the tycoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.27,0:11:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but not so from the patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.28,0:11:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you did your job for the money,\Nyou'd have a larger office right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.12,0:11:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. It's {\i1}Over the Rainbow...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.43,0:11:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.60,0:11:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.87,0:12:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.94,0:12:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's go get\Nsomething to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.52,0:12:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to eat for yourself and\Nthe new life that's going to be born.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.09,0:12:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our baby's moving around\Nbecause it's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.06,0:12:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Missus...\NWhat restaurant shall we go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.60,0:12:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.63,0:12:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What about that place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he disappeared\Ninto the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.07,0:12:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the last time\NI saw Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.21,0:12:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I tell my story from\Nthe beginning once more?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.29,0:12:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I will keep telling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.15,0:12:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I will keep telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.96,0:13:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the fourth lawyer\Nwho's come to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But they all want me admit to part of\Nthe crime and try to lighten my sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.04,0:13:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all they talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.27,0:13:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem like you don't want\Nto prove your innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.98,0:13:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but rather prove the existence\Nof the young man called Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.28,0:13:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.08,0:13:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you don't\Nreally need a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.66,0:13:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.63,0:13:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When did this really begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.76,0:13:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, a boy with a gunshot\Nwound to his head was carried in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.33,0:13:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, didn't something\Nhappen before that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A Turkish woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.18,0:13:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Bring back my husband!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.01,0:13:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After all, people's live\Naren't created equal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.42,0:13:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,People's lives are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.16,0:14:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...\Nif what I did was the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.43,0:14:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if my patients\Nare good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.23,0:14:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My sin is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My sin is saving that boy's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.27,0:14:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.11,0:14:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Does a doctor have the right\Nto choose who to save
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.35,0:14:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,based on whether\Nhis patient is good or evil?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.08,0:14:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}People's lives\Naren't created equal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.49,0:14:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They're equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.52,0:14:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, I can't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.06,0:14:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same with lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.13,0:14:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't tell if the accused\Nis good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a list of names here of the\Npeople who asked me to represent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.14,0:14:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Michail Hotter, Mr. Stephan Crump,\NMr. Franz Kieffer, Mr. Rudolf Huber...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.38,0:15:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kieffer... Mr. Huber.. .\NThey are doing well, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.48,0:15:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Horst Henschel,\NMr. Harmut Hess...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.82,0:15:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Mr. Hess. .. I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.82,0:15:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if he's living happily\Nwith his grandchild.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.16,0:15:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Time's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.20,0:15:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.30,0:15:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.57,0:15:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take up your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.91,0:15:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even lawyers can't tell\Nif people are good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I can do when\NI defend someone is to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,One more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.16,0:15:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "One more !"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.23,0:15:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.06,0:15:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When did this place\Nstart refusing my orders?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.31,0:16:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.38,0:16:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You just laughed,\Ndidn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.32,0:16:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You laughed!\NYou looked at me and laughed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.96,0:16:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.42,0:16:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You used to come to my house often\Nand bow your head,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.23,0:16:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. North Rhine West Bank\Nassistant branch manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.83,0:16:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What a look!\NI've finally came back...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann has\Ncome back to Düsseldorf!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.08,0:16:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for agreeing\Nto meet me, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been calling you\Never since I heard that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.22,0:16:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma had obtained\Nlegal representation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.39,0:16:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I'm usually not home. I've\Nbeen running around investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.96,0:16:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Investigating?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.06,0:16:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I've been visiting Dr. Tenma's\Nformer patients who are supporting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.47,0:16:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What did they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that Dr. Tenma\Nis a wonderful doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.84,0:17:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So did you get any\Nimportant testimonies?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'd like if I could connect a\Ntestimony to Dr. Tenma's alibi, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in order to prove\NTenma's innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.92,0:17:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to prove\NJohan's existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.49,0:17:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma said that he was going to\Nshoot the young man named Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.53,0:17:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to cover up\Nthat testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.10,0:17:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That event is the only one\Nthat can prove Johan exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.67,0:17:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma is innocent no matter\Nif Johan exists or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.28,0:17:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Dr. Reichwein.\NThis country only wants a scapegoat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,My child will be born soon.\NI want true justice for my child as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There are judges and lawyers who will\Nplace the guilt on an innocent person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.33,0:18:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,just so that they can wrap up\Ntheir cases quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.17,0:18:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This entire country must repent\Nfor its lack of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what's important!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.70,0:18:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.67,0:18:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm searching for\Nsomeone right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.25,0:18:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She might know\Nsomething important.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.92,0:18:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.42,0:18:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma's former fiancée...\NEva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.52,0:18:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong,\NDr. Reichwein?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.69,0:18:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.73,0:18:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.63,0:18:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman came with me\Nto this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.10,0:18:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is always laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.44,0:18:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughing at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.01,0:18:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.32,0:18:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm listening.\NHow annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.89,0:18:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to meet\NTenma's lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.99,0:19:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.06,0:19:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you the other day?\NI tried to shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.10,0:19:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised when\Nyou told me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.24,0:19:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you didn't shoot him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.64,0:19:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I didn't shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.44,0:19:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.74,0:19:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's problematic for me\Nif he dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.81,0:19:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let the man who ruined my life\Ndie that easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.49,0:19:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got to be put in jail for the rest\Nof his life and regret what he did!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.93,0:19:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Regret for the rest of his life\Nthat he dumped me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.48,0:19:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.04,0:20:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\NWere you dreaming?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.54,0:20:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Three gunshots.\NI didn't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.38,0:20:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I.. .didn't see the blond haired man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.92,0:20:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.32,0:20:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.53,0:20:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over the Rainbow...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.73,0:20:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A song that symbolizes\Nthe free world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.60,0:20:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann, your wife\Nhas gone into labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:20:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been taken to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.44,0:21:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.41,0:21:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.71,0:21:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Klinger...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Contact Mr. Baul immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.81,0:21:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to\Nsee Dr. Tenma right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.72,0:21:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but ask him if he can\Nsee Dr. Tenma instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.62,0:21:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.\NI'm Baul.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.32,0:21:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to see you today.\NHow are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.86,0:21:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you getting enough sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.06,0:21:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.16,0:21:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.73,0:21:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.80,0:21:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm actually right handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.67,0:21:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't get used to holding\Na pen with my left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.51,0:21:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My right hand doesn't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.52,0:21:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember me?\NI've lost some weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.02,0:21:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm even impressed with myself\Nthat I escaped that sea of fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.60,0:21:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You really shot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.11,0:22:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.08,0:22:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still hard using pens, but it's gotten\Nquite used to handling a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.46,0:22:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I was thinking of killing your former fiancée... Eva Heinemann.
